Part 4: Adaptive Reskilling Engine

12-Month Internal Transformation Program

4.1 Phase Breakdown with Success Metrics

Phase 1: Cognitive Alignment (Months 1-3)

```
Target Roles: High-performing analysts, process managers, subject matter experts

Curriculum:
Week 1-4: Foundations of Autonomous Systems
• How AKCE, AEOA, and EVC work together
• Basic semantic engineering principles
• Introduction to agent-based thinking

Week 5-8: Role-Specialized Foundations
• For Curator track: Ontology design, knowledge graph basics
• For Engineer track: API orchestration, basic control theory

Week 9-12: Shadow Tasks
• Curators: Tag 100 critical documents with confidence scores
• Engineers: Map 50 key processes into decision trees

Success Metrics:
• 80% pass rate on foundational certification
• Completion of shadow tasks with 90% accuracy
• Positive engagement scores (>4.0/5.0)
```

Phase 2: Collaborative Sandboxing (Months 4-6)

```
Environment: Digital twin of one department (e.g., Customer Service)

Exercise Structure:
Week 1: Policy Implementation
• Curators load new customer service policies into AKCE
• Engineers configure AEOA agents to execute based on policies

Week 2-3: Execution & Observation
• Run simulated customer interactions
• Monitor where agents succeed/fail
• Identify knowledge-action gaps

Week 4-6: Iterative Improvement
• Daily standups to review failures
• Redesign knowledge structures and agent behaviors
• Measure improvement week-over-week

Success Metrics:
• Policy comprehension accuracy: >90%
• Agent success rate: >85%
• Reduction in human interventions: 40% over 6 weeks
```

Phase 3: Supervised Agency (Months 7-9)

```
Deployment Scope: Low-risk internal workflows
• IT ticketing and resolution
• HR onboarding coordination
• Internal reporting generation
• Meeting scheduling and coordination

Human Role: Validation Checkpoint
• System proposes actions
• Trainee reviews and approves/corrects
• Corrections feed learning loop

Success Metrics:
• Human intervention rate decreases weekly
• System accuracy improves with fewer corrections
• Trainee efficiency increases (more reviews per hour)
```

Phase 4: Certification & Role Pivot (Months 10-12)

```
Final Assessment: Live Business Challenge
• Real business problem requiring autonomous solution
• 48-hour timeframe to design and implement
• Evaluation by senior leadership and existing experts

Certification Requirements:
• Technical competency demonstration
• Business impact analysis
• Ethical considerations addressed
• Learning loop designed

Outcome: Official role transition with:
• New title and job description
• Adjusted compensation (15-25% increase)
• Clear career progression path
• Ongoing development plan
```

